# GTEx Download Instructions

This document describes how to download the GTEx gene-level TPM expression files required to run the mitochondrial signature scoring pipeline.

## Required GTEx data

This workflow uses **GTEx Analysis V11 gene-level TPM files** from normal human tissues.

For the representative analysis, download the following tissue-specific files:

```text
gene_tpm_v11_heart_atrial_appendage.gct.gz
gene_tpm_v11_heart_left_ventricle.gct.gz
gene_tpm_v11_muscle_skeletal.gct.gz
gene_tpm_v11_whole_blood.gct.gz
```

These files correspond to:

```text
Heart - Atrial Appendage
Heart - Left Ventricle
Muscle - Skeletal
Whole Blood
```

## Where to download

Go to the GTEx Portal:

```text
https://gtexportal.org/home/datasets
```

Then navigate to:

```text
Adult GTEx
→ Bulk Tissue Expression
→ GTEx Analysis V11
→ Gene TPMs by tissue
```

Download the four tissue-specific gene TPM files listed above.

## Where to place the files

After download, place the files in a local folder named:

```text
GTEx_data/
```

The expected structure is:

```text
mitochondrial-signature-scoring/
│
├── GTEx_data/
│   ├── gene_tpm_v11_heart_atrial_appendage.gct.gz
│   ├── gene_tpm_v11_heart_left_ventricle.gct.gz
│   ├── gene_tpm_v11_muscle_skeletal.gct.gz
│   └── gene_tpm_v11_whole_blood.gct.gz
│
├── data/
│   └── signatures/
│       ├── MitoAll.xlsx
│       └── MitoOnly.xlsx
│
└── Rscript/
    └── run_pipeline.R
```

## Important notes

GTEx expression files are not included in this repository because of file size.

Do not rename the GTEx sample identifiers inside the files. The pipeline expects the original sample IDs to be preserved.

Use **gene-level TPM files**, not transcript-level TPM files, because the MitoAll and MitoOnly signatures are defined at the gene-symbol level.

The pipeline expects standard GTEx `.gct.gz` files containing gene identifiers, gene symbols, and sample-level expression values.

## Input file checklist

Before running the pipeline, confirm that these files exist:

```text
GTEx_data/gene_tpm_v11_heart_atrial_appendage.gct.gz
GTEx_data/gene_tpm_v11_heart_left_ventricle.gct.gz
GTEx_data/gene_tpm_v11_muscle_skeletal.gct.gz
GTEx_data/gene_tpm_v11_whole_blood.gct.gz
```

Also confirm that the mitochondrial signature files exist:

```text
data/signatures/MitoAll.xlsx
data/signatures/MitoOnly.xlsx
```

Each signature file must contain a column named:

```text
Gene name
```

## Running the pipeline

After placing the GTEx files in `GTEx_data/`, run:

```r
source("Rscript/run_pipeline.R")
```

The workflow will import the GTEx TPM matrices, harmonize gene symbols, calculate MitoAll and MitoOnly scores, assess gene recovery, perform statistical comparisons, and generate output tables and figures.
